```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text Input Form</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Text Input Form</h1>
    <form id="textForm">
        <label for="userText">Enter your text:</label><br>
        <textarea id="userText" name="userText" rows="4" cols="50"></textarea><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>

    <h2>Saved Text</h2>
    <div id="savedText"></div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('textForm').addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
            event.preventDefault();
            const userText = document.getElementById('userText').value;
            localStorage.setItem('savedText', userText);
            document.getElementById('savedText').innerText = userText;
        });

        // Load saved text from local storage when the page loads
        window.onload = function() {
            const savedText = localStorage.getItem('savedText');
            if (savedText) {
                document.getElementById('savedText').innerText = savedText;
            }
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This script creates a form with a textarea for users to input text. When the form is submitted, the text is saved to local storage and displayed on the page. The saved text is also loaded from local storage when the page is loaded.

